  "dct_title_s": "Uganda GIS Maps and Data, 2000-2010",
  "dct_description_sm": [
    "Uganda GIS Maps and Data is a collection of vector shapefiles, which contain administrative boundary data for national, county, sub-county, sub-regional areas as well as point location data for villages, towns, district centers, schools and healthcare centers. Feature data such as roads, lakes, rivers, water sources, and land use types are also included. This dataset includes 2005 poverty statistics for 855 rural subcounties.",
    "System requirements: Geographic Information Systems (GIS) software that reads ESRI shapefile format."
  ],
